  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static8/politics/2024/06/21/seeing-is-believing-not-necessarily-when-it-comes-to-video-clips-of-biden-and-trump.webp" alt="Seeing is believing? Not necessarily when it comes to video clips of Biden and Trump"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Seeing is believing? Not necessarily when it comes to video clips of Biden and Trump</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      NEW YORK (AP) — President Joe Biden’s simple act of sitting down while commemorating the 80th anniversary of D-Day in Normandy, France, gained more attention than the ceremony itself in some circles as social media users shared a shortened version of the clip to falsely claim he was reaching for a n
      <a itemprop="url" href="/politics/2024/06/21/seeing-is-believing-not-necessarily-when-it-comes-to-video-clips-of-biden-and-trump/"  >(MELISSA GOLDIN and ALI SWENSON, Associated Press, KGET 17, NBC)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div></div><div class="column vcwi"><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Fri, 21 Jun 2024 14:30:53 +0000">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Fri, 21 Jun 2024 14:30:53 +0000">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Zach Schonfeld, WFLA, NBC">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static8/politics/2024/06/21/supreme-court-upholds-federal-gun-possession-ban-for-domestic-abusers.webp" alt="Supreme Court upholds federal law banning domestic abusers from owning guns"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Supreme Court upholds federal law banning domestic abusers from owning guns</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      The Supreme Court in an 8-1 decision Friday upheld a federal law that disarms people under domestic violence restraining orders, ruling it complies with the court’s recent expansion of Second Amendment rights.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/politics/2024/06/21/supreme-court-upholds-federal-gun-possession-ban-for-domestic-abusers/"  >(Zach Schonfeld, WFLA, NBC)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
